<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910118-0088</DOCNO><DOCID>910118-0088.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- AB Volvo:   Division Plans to Dismiss   1,550 Workers at 6 Plants</HL><DATE>01/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   VOLVY</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   Volvo Car Corp., a unit of AB Volvo, said it will givenotice of dismissal to the labor boards for 1,550 workers atsix of the company's production plants.   The Swedish company said it can no longer fulfill itsprevious goal of reducing its work force through normal staffturnover. It said it was necessary to give notice ofdismissal because of the shortage of work in the face ofdeclining sales and growing car stocks.</LP><TEXT>   The dismissals are part of a plan announced earlier toreduce AB Volvo's total work force by 4,500 employees overthe next year. The company said it hopes to minimize thenumber of dismissals through retraining programs,transferring staff and lending out staff between variousunits.   The company said union discussions will take place locallyat each of the six plants affected.</TEXT></DOC>